    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for the closing and i'm kinda confused. what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the house purchase?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of a house purchase, is essentially a neutral third-party holding place for funds and documents. It's a safe mechanism to ensure that both you and the seller fulfill your end of the bargain before the property officially transfers. You need it because it protects both parties, ensuring that the seller doesn't receive the money until the title is properly transferred to you, and you don't hand over the funds until you have the keys.",
      "source": "target",
