      "content": "The money is held by a licensed escrow company or title company, which is a specialized, regulated entity, not just a regular bank account. These professionals are strictly bound by escrow regulations, which means they are legally required to keep the funds separate from their own operating money. This separation is crucial because it minimizes the risk of the funds being misused, keeping your large sums safe throughout the transaction.",
